net.opentsdb.uid

Class UniqueIdWhitelistFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.opentsdb.uid.UniqueIdFilterPlugin
      • net.opentsdb.uid.UniqueIdWhitelistFilter

  • public class UniqueIdWhitelistFilter
extends UniqueIdFilterPlugin
    A UID filter implementation using regular expression based whitelists. Multiple regular expressions can be provided in the configuration file with a configurable delimiter. Each expression is compiled into a list per UID type and when a new UID passes through the filter, each expression in the list is compared to make sure the name satisfies all expressions.

      • allowUIDAssignment

        public com.stumbleupon.async.Deferred<Boolean> allowUIDAssignment(UniqueId.UniqueIdType type,
                                                                  String value,
                                                                  String metric,
                                                                  Map<String,String> tags)
        Description copied from class: UniqueIdFilterPlugin
        Determine whether or not the UID should be assigned. If the UID should not be assigned a value, the implementation can return false or an exception in the deferred object. Otherwise it should return true and the UID will proceed with assignment. NOTE: In some cases the metric and tags may be null, particularly if the synchronous APIs were called. In such a situation, make sure the implementation handles it properly.
        Specified by:
        allowUIDAssignment in class UniqueIdFilterPlugin
        Parameters:
        type - The type of UID being assigned
        value - The string value of the UID
        metric - The metric name associated with the UID for assignment
        tags - The tag set associated with the UID
        Returns:
        True if the UID should be assigned, false if not.
